cs.NI, cs.MA, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the performance of a backscatter tag-to-tag network and the development of a communication protocol suite. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of multiple tags to extend the coverage of the network. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper discusses the design of a low-power listening MAC protocol. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the control of link quality in the network. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on security or cryptography, but it may be relevant in the context of securing the communication in the network.
